TITLE: Custom API Configuration - Amis Form (JSON Schema)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure the `api` property as an object to customize the HTTP method (PUT), URL, and request body using data mapping. In this example, a PUT request is sent to `/api/mock2/page/initData` with the form data and an additional `_from` field.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/index.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "initApi": {
      "method": "put",
      "url": "/api/mock2/page/initData",
      "data": {
        "&": "$$$$",
        "_from": "browser"
      }
    },
    "title": "用户信息",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "name",
        "label": "姓名"
      },
      {
        "type": "input-email",
        "name": "email",
        "label": "邮箱"
      }
    ]
  }
```

