TITLE: Enabling Row Selection in Amis CRUD
DESCRIPTION: This JSON configures an Amis CRUD component to enable row selection. The `selectable` property is set to `true`, allowing users to select rows. A button in the `headerToolbar` displays the selected items in a toast message when at least one item is selected.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/crud.md#_snippet_85

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "crud",
    "api": "/api/mock2/sample",
    "syncLocation": false,
    "selectable": true,
    "headerToolbar": [
      {
        "type": "button",
        "label": "按钮",
        "visibleOn": "${selectedItems.length}",
        "actionType": "toast",
        "toast": {
          "items": [
            {
              "level": "info",
              "body": "${selectedItems|json}"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ],
    "columns": [
        {
            "name": "id",
            "label": "ID"
        },
        {
            "name": "engine",
            "label": "Rendering engine"
        },
        {
            "name": "browser",
            "label": "Browser"
        },
        {
            "name": "platform",
            "label": "Platform(s)"
        },
        {
            "name": "version",
            "label": "Engine version"
        },
        {
            "name": "grade",
            "label": "CSS grade"
        }
    ]
}
```

