TITLE: AMIS Form Validation Example
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to validate an AMIS form using the `validate` action. A button triggers form validation, and the validation result is displayed in a static input-text field. The form includes required fields and email validation to showcase different validation scenarios. The result is cached in `${event.data.validateResult}`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/index.md#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
[  {
    "type": "button",
    "label": "校验表单",
    className: "mb-2",
    "onEvent": {
        "click": {
            "actions": [
              {
                "actionType": "validate",
                "componentId": "form_validate",
                "outputVar": "form_validate_result"
              },
              {
                "actionType": "setValue",
                "componentId": "validate_info",
                "args": {
                  "value": "${event.data.form_validate_result|json}"
                }
              }
            ]
        }
    }
  },
  {
    type: 'input-text',
    name: 'validate_info',
    id: 'validate_info',
    label: '校验结果：',
    static: true
  },
  {
    "type": "form",
    "id": "form_validate",
    "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "name",
        "label": "姓名：",
        "required": true
      },
      {
        "name": "email",
        "type": "input-text",
        "label": "邮箱：",
        "required": true,
        "validations": {
          "isEmail": true
        }
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

