TITLE: Form Submission with API - Amis Form (JSON Schema)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates configuring an Amis Form to submit data to an API endpoint using the `api` property.  The API endpoint `/api/saveForm` will receive the form data when the form is submitted via a POST request. The form data is serialized as a JSON object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/index.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "api": "/api/saveForm",
    "title": "用户信息",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "name",
        "label": "姓名"
      },
      {
        "type": "input-email",
        "name": "email",
        "label": "邮箱"
      }
    ]
  }
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring API data with Pagination Parameters (JSON)
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet shows how to pass pagination parameters, like `pageNo` and `pageSize`, within the `data` property of the `api` configuration in Amis. It uses data mapping `${page}` and `${perPage}` to dynamically set the values based on user interaction within the CRUD component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/crud.md#_snippet_40

