TITLE: Configuring init and inited Events in Amis - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure 'init' and 'inited' events in an Amis page component.  The 'init' event displays a simple toast message. The 'inited' event displays the response data from the 'initApi' request as a JSON string in a toast message. It shows how to access event data using the `${event.data.responseData|json}` syntax.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/page.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "initApi": "/api/mock2/page/initData",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "tpl",
      "tpl": "当前时间是：${date}"
    }
  ],
  "onEvent": {
    "init": {
      "actions": [
        {
          "actionType": "toast",
          "args": {
            "msgType": "info",
            "msg": "init"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "inited": {
      "actions": [
        {
          "actionType": "toast",
          "args": {
            "msgType": "info",
            "msg": "${event.data.responseData|json}"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

