TITLE: Custom Search Filter Function in Select (JSON, JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define a custom search filter function for an Amis select component using `filterOption`. The JavaScript function allows you to control how options are filtered based on the input value. It allows searching across the value, label, and weapon properties of the options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/select.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "body": [
    {
      "label": "带搜索",
      "type": "select",
      "name": "a",
      "selectMode": "chained",
      "searchable": true,
      "filterOption": "return options.filter(({value, label, weapon}) => value?.includes(inputValue) || label?.includes(inputValue) || weapon?.includes(inputValue));",
