TITLE: Reloading CRUD with different button types - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases three ways to trigger a CRUD refresh: a `reload` type button within the CRUD's toolbar, an `action` type button targeting the CRUD by its name, and a button outside the CRUD triggering a `reload` action via `onEvent`. Each approach requires specifying the CRUD component to refresh, either implicitly or via `target` or `componentId`. Note that the refresh action resets the selected items by default, even with `keepItemSelectionOnPageChange` set to `true`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/crud.md#_snippet_73

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
