TITLE: AMIS Form Submit Failure Event Example
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to handle the submitFail event of an AMIS form. It defines an invalid API endpoint to simulate a failed submission and uses the `setValue` action to display the error data in a static input-text field. The error data from the API response is shown. Like the previous example, it uses a basic form with name and email, but with an endpoint designed to fail.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/index.md#_snippet_36

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
[  {
    "type": "form",
    "title": "尝试提交表单",
    "api": "/api/mock2/form/x",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "name",
        "label": "姓名",
        "value": "amis"
      },
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "email",
        "label": "邮箱",
        "value": "amis@baidu.com"
      }
    ],
    "onEvent": {
      "submitFail": {
        "actions": [
          {
            "actionType": "setValue",
            "componentId": "submit_fail_text",
            "args": {
              "value": "${event.data.error|json}"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "input-text",
    "id": "submit_fail_text",
    "static": true,
    "name": "tip",
    "label": "上下文"
  }
]
```

