TITLE: Custom Component Props Usage - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to access and use the `props` argument provided to the Custom component's lifecycle methods. It demonstrates using `props.onAction` to trigger an action (in this case, a dialog) and `props.env.notify` to display a notification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/custom.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
onMount: (dom, data, onChange, props) => {
  const button = document.createElement('button');
  button.innerText = '点击修改姓名';
  button.onclick = event => {
    onChange('new name', 'name');
    props.onAction(
      event,
      {
        type: 'action',
        label: '弹个框',
        actionType: 'dialog',
        dialog: {
          title: '弹框',
          body: 'Hello World!'
        }
      },
      {} // 这是 data
    );
    event.preventDefault();
  };
  dom.appendChild(button);
};
```

