TITLE: Filtering Column Data in Amis
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure column filtering in an Amis CRUD component. When a filter is applied to the 'Rendering engine' column, a toast notification will display the filter name and value. The `filterable` property within the column definition enables this functionality, providing filter options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/crud.md#_snippet_89

LANGUAGE: schema
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "body": {
    "type": "crud",
    "api": "/api/mock2/sample",
    "syncLocation": false,
    "onEvent": {
        "columnFilter": {
            "actions": [
                {
                    "actionType": "toast",
                    "args": {
                    "msgType": "info",
                    "msg": "filterName：${event.data.filterName},filterValue：${event.data.filterValue}"
