TITLE: Updating Records in Input Table
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to update specific rows in an Amis input table by specifying either the `index` or a `condition`. The `index` updates rows at specific indices, while the `condition` updates rows that meet specified criteria, defined either as a Javascript expression or as a ConditionBuilder object. The `componentId` refers to the `id` of the `input-table` to be modified. The `actionType` is `setValue`.
