TITLE: Setting Tabs Dynamically - Amis JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON configuration demonstrates how to dynamically set the active tab in an Amis Tabs component using a radios input. The `activeKey` property is bound to the `key` data using the `toInt` filter to ensure the value is an integer.  The `key` data value controls which tab is active. The `radios` component allows the user to select the active tab.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/tabs.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
    "data": {
    "key": 2
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "radios",
      "name": "key",
      "mode": "inline",
      "label": "激活的选项卡",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Tab 1",
          "value": 0
        },
        {
          "label": "Tab 2",
          "value": 1
        },
        {
          "label": "Tab 3",
          "value": 2
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tabs",
      "activeKey": "${key|toInt}",
      "tabs": [
        {
          "title": "Tab 1",
          "tab": "Content 1"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tab 2",
          "tab": "Content 2"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tab 3",
          "tab": "Content 3"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

