TITLE: Editable Content via Column Type - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to make InputTable cells directly editable by setting the `type` property within a column's configuration.  For example, `type: "input-text"` turns the column into a text input, while `type: "select"` creates a dropdown select. The `needConfirm: false` property is suggested to disable confirmation dialogs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-table.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "data": {
    "table": [
      {
        "a": "a1",
        "b": "b1"
      },
      {
        "a": "a2",
        "b": "b2"
      },
      {
        "a": "a3",
        "b": "b3"
      }
    ]
  },
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-table",
      "name": "table",
      "label": "Table",
      "addable": true,
      "needConfirm": false,
      "columns": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "name": "a",
          "type": "input-text"
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "name": "b",
          "type": "select",
          "options": [
            "b1", "b2", "b3"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

