TITLE: Custom Filtering with MatchFunc - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to implement custom filtering logic for the InputTable using the `matchFunc` property.  `matchFunc` takes a JavaScript function that allows complex filter criteria based on the table data, query, and column configurations. This enables more sophisticated filtering beyond simple text matching.  It requires providing JavaScript code as a string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-table.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "initApi": "/api/mock2/sample",
  "body": [
    {
      "type":"input-table",
      "perPage": 10,
      "name":"rows",
      "addable": true,
      "matchFunc": "const query = options.query;if (query.version === '>=20') {items = items.filter(item => parseFloat(item.version) >= 20);} else if (query.version ==='<20') {items = items.filter(item => parseFloat(item.version) < 20);}return items;",
      "columns":[
        {
          "name": "id",
          "label": "ID"
        },
        {
          "name": "grade",
          "label": "CSS grade"
        },
        {
          "name": "version",
          "label": "Version",
          "filterable": {
            "options": [
              ">=20",
              "<20"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

