TITLE: Table2 Pre-selected Rows with Expression
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates pre-selecting rows based on an expression using `selectedRowKeysExpr` within the `rowSelection` configuration. This allows for dynamic selection based on row data. The table data comes from a service API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/table2.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "api": "/api/sample?perPage=5",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "table2",
      "source": "$rows",
      "rowSelection": {
        "type": "checkbox",
        "keyField": "id",
        "selectedRowKeysExpr": "data.record.id === 1"
      },
      "columns": [
        {
          "title": "ID",
          "name": "id"
        },
        {
          "title": "Engine",
          "name": "engine"
        },
        {
          "title": "Version",
          "name": "version"
        },
        {
          "title": "Browser",
          "name": "browser"
        },
        {
          "title": "Operation",
          "name": "operation",
          "type": "button",
          "label": "删除",
          "size": "sm"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

