TITLE: Input-Tree: Implementing Lazy Loading (defer, deferApi)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to implement lazy loading for large trees. The `defer` property is set to `true` for nodes that should be loaded on demand, and the `deferApi` property specifies the API endpoint to fetch the child nodes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-tree.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "debug": true,
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-tree",
      "name": "tree",
      "label": "Tree",
      "deferApi": "/api/mock2/form/deferOptions?label=${label}&waitSeconds=2",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Folder A",
          "value": 1,
          "collapsed": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "label": "file A",
              "value": 2
            },
            {
              "label": "file B",
              "value": 3
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "这下面是懒加载的",
          "value": 4,
          "defer": true
        },
        {
          "label": "file D",
          "value": 5
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

