TITLE: Conditional Property Visibility - JSON
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to conditionally show or hide attributes in the property table using `visibleOn` or `hiddenOn`. This example shows how to conditionally hide the 'memory' item if the cpu is not greater than 1. This dynamic display based on expressions can improve the user experience by only showing relevant information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/property.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "property",
  "items": [
    {
      "label": "cpu",
      "content": "1 core"
    },
    {
      "label": "memory",
      "content": "4G",
      "visibleOn": "data.cpu > 1"
    },
    {
      "label": "network",
      "content": "4M",
      "span": 2
    }
  ]
}
```

