TITLE: Synchronizing Internal Form Items in Combo
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to synchronize changes in the parent data domain with the internal form items of the Amis Combo component. To enable synchronization, set `strictMode` to `false` and define the `syncFields` array, listing the variable names that should be synchronized.  This ensures that changes to the parent's `super_text` field are reflected within the combo's `super_text` input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/combo.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "debug": true,
  "mode": "horizontal",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "body": [
    {
        "type": "input-text",
        "label": "父级文本框",
        "name": "super_text",
        "value": "123"
    },
    {
        "type": "combo",
        "name": "combo2",
        "label": "可获取父级数据",
        "multiple": true,
        "canAccessSuperData": true,
        "items": [
            {
                "name": "super_text",
                "type": "input-text"
            }
        ]
    }
  ]
}
```

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "debug": true,
  "mode": "horizontal",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "body": [
    {
        "type": "input-text",
        "label": "父级文本框",
        "name": "super_text",
        "value": "123"
    },
    {
        "type": "combo",
        "name": "combo2",
