TITLE: Manual API Trigger with Reload Action
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to manually trigger an API request for a select component using a button with a reload action.  The `addOn` property of the input-text component defines a button that, when clicked, triggers a `reload` action on the select component named 'my_form.select'. The data from the input text field is passed to the API request as a query parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/linkage.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "name": "my_form",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "keyword",
        "addOn": {
          "label": "搜索",
          "type": "button",
          "actionType": "reload",
          "target": "my_form.select"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "select",
        "name": "select",
        "label": "Select",
        "source": {
          "method": "get",
          "url": "/api/mock2/form/getOptions?waitSeconds=1",
          "data": {
            "a": "${keyword}"
          }
        }
      }
    ]
}
```

