DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases how to dynamically apply CSS classes to table cells based on data using the `classNameExpr` property. The expression `${ version > 5 ? 'text-danger' : '' }` adds the `text-danger` class to the 'version' cell if the version value is greater than 5. Uses template syntax.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/table2.md#_snippet_57

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "api": "/api/sample?perPage=5",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "table2",
      "source": "$rows",
      "columns": [
        {
          "title": "Engine",
          "name": "engine"
        },
        {
          "title": "Version",
          "name": "version",
          "classNameExpr": "${ version > 5 ? 'text-danger' : '' }"
        },
        {
          "title": "Browser",
          "name": "browser"
        },
        {
          "title": "Operation",
          "name": "operation",
          "type": "button",
          "label": "删除",
          "size": "sm"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

