TITLE: Validation via form item validation API
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to configure form item validation using the `validateApi` property. Each input field, like 'name' and 'email', has its own validation API endpoint. The API is called whenever the input value changes and the API response indicates whether the validation was successful or not.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/formitem.md#_snippet_42

LANGUAGE: schema
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "mode": "horizontal",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "body": [
    {
      "label": "name",
      "type": "input-text",
      "name": "name",
      "required": true,
      "validateApi": "/api/mock2/form/formitemFailed"
    },
    {
      "label": "email",
      "type": "input-text",
      "name": "email",
      "validateApi": "/api/mock2/form/formitemSuccess",
      "required": true
    }
  ]
}
```

