TITLE: Form with Conditional Input Types - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON shows an Amis form configuration that handles multiple types for the same field ('id') using a switch ('idIsNumber').  Based on the switch state, either a text input or a number input is displayed, effectively allowing the 'id' field to accept either string or numeric values.  `hiddenOn` and `visibleOn` properties control which input is shown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/addon.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "mode": "horizontal",
  "body": [
    {
      "name": "idIsNumber",
      "type": "switch",
      "label": "id 是数字类型"
    },
    {
      "name": "id",
      "type": "input-text",
