TITLE: Reload Action Configuration (AMIS Schema)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to configure a button to trigger a `reload` action on a service component. Clicking the button will cause the service with the ID `service-reload` to reload its data by making a new API request. This configuration demonstrates how to refresh a component's data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/service.md#_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
[
  {
    "type": "button",
    "label": "刷新请求",
    "onEvent": {
      "click": {
        "actions": [
          {
            "componentId": "service-reload",
            "actionType": "reload"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "service",
    "id": "service-reload",
    "name": "service-reload",
    "api": "/api/mock2/number/random",
    "body": "现在是：${random}"
  }
]
```

