TITLE: Registering Custom Filter (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to register a custom filter in TypeScript using the `registerFilter` function. The custom filter can then be used in Amis templates just like the built-in filters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/data-mapping.md#_snippet_83

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {registerFilter} from 'amis';

registerFilter('count', (input: string) =>
  typeof input === 'string' ? input.length : 0
);

```

