TITLE: Configuring Searchable Options for Input-Tree (AMIS)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to enable searching within the options of an AMIS Input-Tree component. Setting `"searchable": true` allows users to search the current data source. The `searchConfig` can be used to customize the search behavior. A `deferApi` is used to load options dynamically. Requires AMIS version 2.8.0 or higher.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-tree.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-tree",
      "name": "tree",
      "label": "Tree",
      "deferApi": "/api/mock2/form/deferOptions?label=${label}&waitSeconds=2",
      "searchable": true,
      "searchConfig": {
        "sticky": true
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Folder A",
          "value": 1,
          "collapsed": true,
          "children": [
            {
              "label": "file A",
              "value": 2
            },
            {
              "label": "file B",
              "value": 3
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "这下面是懒加载的",
          "value": 4,
          "defer": true
        },
        {
          "label": "file D",
          "value": 5
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

