TITLE: IsTrue Filter Example
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the `isTrue` filter within an Amis page configuration to display different text based on the boolean values of `value1` and `value2`. It utilizes the `tpl` component to render the output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/data-mapping.md#_snippet_68

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "value1": true,
    "value2": false
  },
  "body": [
    {
        "type": "tpl",
        "tpl": "value1：${value1|isTrue:'是真':'是假'}" // 输出: value是真
    },
    {
        "type": "divider"
    },
    {
        "type": "tpl",
        "tpl": "value2：${value2|isTrue:'是真':'是假'}" // 输出: value是真
    }
  ]
}
```

