TITLE: Custom API Messages Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates configuring custom success and failure messages for an AMIS API using the `messages` property. These messages will be displayed to the user based on the API request's outcome, improving the user experience by providing more informative feedback.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/types/api.md#_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "api": {
        "method": "post",
        "url": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
        "data": {
            "myName": "${name}",
            "myEmail": "${email}"
        },
        "messages": {
          "success": '好耶，成功了！',
          "failed": '糟糕，失败了！'
        }

    },
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "name": "name",
        "label": "姓名："
      },
      {
        "name": "email",
        "type": "input-email",
        "label": "邮箱："
      }
    ]
}
```

