TITLE: Component Visibility and State Control
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates controlling the visibility and disabled state of form items based on the value of a radio button.  The `visibleOn` property controls whether the `text1` input is displayed, while `disabledOn` controls whether `text2` is disabled. Expressions are used to define the conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/linkage.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "body": [
        {
            "type": "radios",
            "name": "foo",
            "label": false,
            "options": [
                {
                    "label": "类型1",
                    "value": 1
                },
                {
                    "label": "类型2",
                    "value": 2
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "input-text",
            "name": "text1",
            "label": false,
            "placeholder": "选中 类型1 时可见",
            "visibleOn": "${foo == 1}"
        },
        {
            "type": "input-text",
            "name": "text2",
            "label": false,
            "placeholder": "选中 类型2 时不可点",
            "disabledOn": "${foo == 2}"
        }
    ]
}
```

