DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to implement form-level validation using the `rules` property.  The example validates that fields `a` and `b` cannot both have values at the same time using an expression.  If both fields have values, an error message will be displayed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/index.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": "/api/form/saveForm",
  "rules": [
    {
      "rule": "!(data.a && data.b)",
      "message": "a 和 b 不能同时有值"
    }
  ],
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "name": "a",
      "label": "A"
    },
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "name": "b",
      "label": "B"
    }
  ]
}
```

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
