TITLE: Configuring Nav with 'click' Event
DESCRIPTION: Provides an example of configuring a Nav component with an `onEvent` handler for the `click` event.  The example showcases how to display a toast message when a navigation item is clicked, indicating the label of the clicked item. Requires amis.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/nav.md#_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "nav",
  "stacked": true,
  "links": [
    {
      "label": "Nav 1",
      "icon": "fa fa-user"
    },
    {
      "label": "Nav 2",
      "children": [
        {
          "label": "Nav 2-1",
          "children": [
            {
              "label": "Nav 2-1-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "Nav 2-2"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Nav 3"
    }
  ],
  "onEvent": {
    "click": {
      "actions": [
        {
          "actionType": "toast",
          "args": {
            "msg": "${event.data.item.label}被点击了，但不一定选中"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: AMIS Clear Action Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates the configuration of the 'clear' action in AMIS. It defines a form with a switch and a button. Clicking the button triggers the 'clear' action on the switch component, effectively clearing its value.  The componentId links the button action to the specific switch component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/switch.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "debug": true,
    "body": [
        {
            "name": "switch",
            "label": "开关",
            "type": "switch",
            "id": "clear_text"
        },
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": "清空",
            "onEvent": {
                "click": {
                    "actions": [
                        {
                            "actionType": "clear",
                            "componentId": "clear_text"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Select Component with Dynamic Options via Data Mapping
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to populate a select component dynamically using data mapping. The `source` attribute references a variable (`items`) within the current data scope, which contains the options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/options.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "data": {
        "items": [
            {
                "label":"A",
                "value":"a"
            },
            {
                "label":"B",
                "value":"b"
            },
            {
                "label":"C",
                "value":"c"
            }
        ]
    },
    "body": [
        {
            "label": "选项",
            "type": "select",
            "name": "select",
            "source": "${items}"
        }
    ]
}
```

