TITLE: AMIS: Updating Records by Condition Builder - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This AMIS configuration updates list items based on a condition defined using a ConditionBuilder.  The `condition` property contains the ConditionBuilder object, specifying the criteria to match. In this example, records with `version` equal to "4" will be updated.  The `conjunction` property specifies how multiple conditions should be combined (e.g., 'and', 'or').
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/list.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
                "actionType": "setValue",
                "componentId": "list_setvalue_item",
                "args": {
                  "value": {
                    "engine": "amis",
                    "browser": "Chrome",
                    "platform": "Mac Pro",
                    "version": "4",
                    "grade": "Y",
                    "badgeText": "你好！",
                    "id": 1234
                  },
                  "condition": {
                      conjunction: 'and',
                      children: [
                        {
                          left: {
                            type: 'field',
                            field: 'version'
                          },
                          op: 'equal',
                          right: "4"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                }
              }
```

