TITLE: Reset Action in Amis Form
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema defines an Amis form with a matrix-checkboxes component and a button to reset the component's value. The 'reset' action, triggered by the button's 'click' event, sets the value of the component with the ID 'reset_text' back to its initial value or the 'resetValue' if it is configured. The reset action effectively reverts the matrix-checkboxes to the values they had when the form was initially loaded.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/matrix-checkboxes.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "debug": true,
    "body": [
        {
          "type": "matrix-checkboxes",
          "name": "matrix",
          "label": "Matrix",
          "rowLabel": "行标题说明",
          "columns": [
            {
              "label": "列1"
            },
            {
              "label": "列2"
            }
          ],
          "rows": [
            {
              "label": "行1"
            },
            {
              "label": "行2"
            }
          ],
          "value": [
            [
              {
                "label": "列1",
                "checked": true
              },
              {
                "label": "列1",
                "checked": false
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "label": "列2",
                "checked": false
              },
              {
                "label": "列2",
                "checked": true
              }
            ]
          ],
          "id": "reset_text"
        },
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": "重置",
            "onEvent": {
                "click": {
                    "actions": [
                        {
                            "actionType": "reset",
                            "componentId": "reset_text"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

