TITLE: Using Expressions with Operators for Default Values - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema demonstrates how to use expressions with operators to calculate default values. The `value` attribute can contain expressions like `${num1 + 2}`.  This allows for dynamic form values based on computations with existing data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/formitem.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-number",
      "label": "num1",
      "name": "num1",
      "value": "123"
    },
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "label": "text",
      "name": "test1",
      "value": "${num1 + 2}",
      "description": "默认值支持表达式运算: ${num1 + 2}"
    }
  ]
}
```

