TITLE: Quick Edit Multiple Form Items - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to configure quickEdit to display multiple form items.  The `quickEdit` property contains a `body` array, where each item is a form element. This lets the user edit multiple columns at the same time within the quick edit form.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/crud.md#_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "crud",
    "syncLocation": false,
    "api": "/api/mock2/sample",
    "quickSaveApi": "/api/mock2/sample/bulkUpdate",
    "columns": [
        {
            "name": "id",
            "label": "ID"
        },
        {
            "name": "grade",
            "label": "CSS grade",
            "quickEdit": {
                "body": [
                    {
                        "type": "select",
                        "name": "grade",
                        "options": [
                            "A",
                            "B",
                            "C",
                            "D",
                            "X"
                        ]
                    },

                    {
                        "label": "id",
                        "type": "input-text",
                        "name": "id"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

