TITLE: Service Init Event Configuration (AMIS Schema)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates configuring the `init` event for an AMIS service component. When the component is initialized and inserted into the DOM, the specified toast action will be triggered, displaying the message "init". The configuration shows how to use `onEvent` to listen for the `init` event and define the corresponding actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/service.md#_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "api": "/api/mock2/page/initData",
  "body": {
    "type": "panel",
    "title": "$title",
    "body": "现在是：${date}"
  },
  "onEvent": {
    "init": {
      "actions": [
        {
          "actionType": "toast",
          "args": {
            "msg": "init"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

