TITLE: Configuring Nav Component with Group Mode
DESCRIPTION: This configuration shows how to group navigation items in the Amis Nav component.  Setting the `mode` property to "group" renders the item as a group title. Group items are defined using the `children` property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/nav.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "nav",
  "stacked": true,
  "links": [
    {
      "label": "Nav 1",
      "to": "/docs/index",
      "icon": "fa fa-user"
    },
    {
      "label": "Nav 2",
      "unfolded": true,
      "mode": "group",
      "children": [
        {
          "label": "Nav 2-1",
          "children": [
            {
              "label": "Nav 2-1-1",
              "to": "/docs/api-2-1-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "Nav 2-2",
          "to": "/docs/api-2-2"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Nav 3",
      "to": "/docs/renderers",
      "mode": "group",
      "children": [
        {
          "label": "Nav 3-1",
          "to": "/docs/api-2-1"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

