TITLE: Configuring WebSocket with responseKey in Amis Service
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure `responseKey` to handle a WebSocket response that is not a JSON object. `responseKey` specifies the key where the raw response should be stored.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/service.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "ws": {
    "url": "ws://localhost:8777?name=${name}",
    "data": {
      "name": "${name}"
    },
    "responseKey": "name"
  },
  "body": {
    "label": "名称",
    "type": "static",
    "name": "name"
  }
}
```

