TITLE: Listening to Tab Switch Events - Amis JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON configuration shows how to listen for tab switch events in the Amis Tabs component. The `onSelect` property is assigned a JavaScript expression that will be executed when a tab is selected.  The current active key will be passed into the alert function call as a parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/tabs.md#_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "tabs",
    "activeKey": "tab2",
    "onSelect": "alert(key)",
