TITLE: Row Linking in Input Table
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases how to create dynamic `id` and `componentId` attributes to link form items within rows of the Amis input table using expressions. The example uses `num1` and `num2` as example fields, where change in `num1` will affect the value of `num2`. The `${index}` expression is used to create unique IDs for each row. The actionType is setValue.
