TITLE: Default WebSocket Fetcher Implementation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript function represents the default WebSocket fetcher implementation used by Amis. It handles connecting to the WebSocket, sending initial data, receiving messages, parsing data, and handling errors. It returns a close function to terminate the connection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/service.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
wsFetcher(ws, onMessage, onError) {
    if (ws) {
      const socket = new WebSocket(ws.url);
      socket.onopen = event => {
        if (ws.body) {
          socket.send(JSON.stringify(ws.body));
        }
      };
      socket.onmessage = event => {
        if (event.data) {
          let data;
          try {
            data = JSON.parse(event.data);
          } catch (error) {}
          if (typeof data !== 'object') {
            let key = ws.responseKey || 'data';
            data = {
              [key]: event.data
            };
          }
          onMessage(data);
        }
      };
      socket.onerror = onError;
      return {
        close: socket.close
      };
    } else {
      return {
        close: () => {}
      };
    }
  }
```

