TITLE: Form Response Adaptor (String)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates configuring a response adaptor (adaptor) as a string within a JSON schema for an AMIS form.  The adaptor intercepts the API response and modifies the payload, mapping the 'code' field to the 'status' field based on its value. This showcases adapting backend responses to AMIS's expected format.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/types/api.md#_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": {
    "method": "post",
    "url": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
    "adaptor": "console.log(context); // 打印上下文数据 \nreturn {\n    ...payload,\n    status: payload.code === 200 ? 0 : payload.code\n}"
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "name": "name",
      "label": "姓名："
    },
    {
      "name": "file",
      "type": "input-file",
      "label": "附件：",
      "asBlob": true
    }
  ]
}
```

