TITLE: Configuring Bottom Single-Row Summary in AMIS Table2
DESCRIPTION: This example configures a single-row summary at the bottom of an AMIS Table2 using the `footSummary` property. The format is similar to `headSummary`.  The example includes configuration of the table columns, data source, and scroll behavior. The `fixed` property is used on the `text` component within the summary and the first column of the table to fix those to the left on horizontal scroll.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/table2.md#_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "api": "/api/sample?perPage=10",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "table2",
      "source": "$rows",
      "bordered": true,
      "scroll": {"y": 200, "x": 1000},
      "columns": [
        {
          "title": "Engine",
          "name": "engine",
          "fixed": "left"
        },
        {
          "title": "Version",
          "name": "version"
        },
        {
          "title": "Grade",
          "name": "grade"
        },
        {
          "title": "Browser",
          "name": "browser"
        },
        {
          "title": "Badge",
          "name": "badgeText"
        },
        {
          "title": "Platform",
          "name": "platform"
        }
      ],
      "footSummary": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "总计",
          "fixed": 'left'
        },
        {
          "type": "tpl",
          "tpl": "测试测试",
          "colSpan": 5
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

