TITLE: BlockRouting Function Signature (Typescript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet defines the function signature for the `blockRouting` function within the Amis environment. It's used to set a hook to prevent routing, usually when a form has unsaved changes. It takes a function that receives the next location as argument and returns void or a string to prevent navigation.  It returns a function to remove the block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/start/getting-started.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
(fn: (nextLocation:any) => void | string) => () => void;
```

