TITLE: Configuring Nav with 'toggled' Event
DESCRIPTION: Presents a configuration example of the Nav component using the `onEvent` handler for the `toggled` event.  This showcases how to display a toast message when a navigation item is expanded or collapsed, based on the item's label and `open` state. Requires amis.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/nav.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "nav",
  "stacked": true,
  "links": [
    {
      "label": "Nav 1",
      "to": "/docs/index",
      "icon": "fa fa-user"
    },
    {
      "label": "Nav 2",
      "unfolded": true,
      "children": [
        {
          "label": "Nav 2-1",
          "children": [
            {
              "label": "Nav 2-1-1",
              "to": "/docs/api-2-1-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "Nav 2-2",
          "to": "/docs/api-2-2"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Nav 3",
      "to": "/docs/renderers"
    }
  ],
  "onEvent": {
    "toggled": {
      "actions": [
        {
          "actionType": "toast",
          "args": {
            "msg": "${event.data.item.label}${event.data.open ? '展开' : '收起'}"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

