TITLE: Configuring Exclusive Switch Action in AMIS
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema demonstrates how to configure an exclusive switch action using `actionType: 'switch'`. The button click event triggers a series of actions, but only the action whose expression evaluates to true will be executed. The example includes three toast actions with different expressions based on `this.branchCont`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/event-action.md#_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: schema
CODE:
```
{
  type: 'page',
  body: {
    type: 'form',
    wrapWithPanel: false,
    data: {
      branchCont: 18
    },
    body: [
      {
        type: 'button',
        label: '只执行动作2',
        level: 'primary',
        onEvent: {
          click: {
            actions: [
              {
                actionType: 'switch',
                children: [
                  {
                    actionType: "toast",
                    args: {
                      msgType: 'info',
                      msg: '动作1',
                      position: 'top-right'
                    },
                    expression: 'this.branchCont > 19',
                    stopPropagation: true // 这里无效，因为条件不成立
                  },
                  {
                    actionType: "toast",
                    args: {
                      msgType: 'info',
                      msg: '动作2',
                      position: 'top-right'
                    },
                    expression: 'this.branchCont > 17'
                  },
                  {
                    actionType: "toast",
                    args: {
                      msgType: 'info',
                      msg: '动作3',
                      position: 'top-right'
                    },
                    expression: 'this.branchCont > 16'
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

