TITLE: Handling AddConfirm Event in Input-Tree
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to handle the `addConfirm` event of the Input-Tree component when the `creatable` property is enabled. It configures the input-tree to allow adding new nodes and sets up an `onEvent` handler to display a toast message showing the newly added node's information when the user confirms the addition. The `event.data.item` is used to access the new item's data, the `addApi` property specifies the API endpoint for adding the new node. Dependencies include the Amis form and input-tree components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-tree.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "debug": true,
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-tree",
      "name": "tree",
      "label": "Tree",
      "creatable": true,
      "removable": true,
      "editable": true,
      "addApi": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
      "onEvent": {
        "addConfirm": {
          "actions": [
            {
              "actionType": "toast",
              "args": {
                "msg": "${event.data.item|json}"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Folder A",
          "value": 1,
          "children": [
            {
              "label": "file A",
              "value": 2
            },
            {
              "label": "file B",
              "value": 3
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "file C",
          "value": 4
        },
        {
          "label": "file D",
          "value": 5
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

