TITLE: Configuring deleteSuccess Event for Input-Table
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the `deleteSuccess` event, which triggers after a successful deletion of a row using the `deleteApi`. A toast message displays the relevant event data.  Enabling `deleteApi` indicates that a server-side call is made upon deletion, and this event handles the success case.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-table.md#_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
  "data": {
    "table": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "a": "a1",
        "b": "b1"
      }
    ]
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "showIndex": true,
      "type": "input-table",
      "name": "table",
      "columns": [
        {
          "name": "a",
          "label": "A"
        },
        {
          "name": "b",
          "label": "B"
        }
      ],
      "removable": true,
      "needConfirm": false,
      "deleteApi": "/api/mock2/table/deleteSuccess",
      "onEvent": {
        "deleteSuccess": {
          "actions": [
            {
              "actionType": "toast",
              "args": {
                "msgType": "info",
                "position": "top-right",
                "title": "deleteSuccess事件",
                "msg": "上下文 ${event.data | json:0}"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

