TITLE: Handling Row Click Event in AMIS Table (JSON)
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema demonstrates how to handle the 'rowClick' event in an AMIS table. The event is triggered when a row is clicked.  The 'rowClick' event triggers a toast message displaying the clicked row's data and index.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/table.md#_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "service",
    "api": "/api/mock2/sample?perPage=10",
    "body": [
        {
            "type": "table",
            "source": "$rows",
            "selectable": true,
            "onEvent": {
                "rowClick": {
                    "actions": [
                        {
                            "actionType": "toast",
                            "args": {
                                "msgType": "info",
                                "msg": "行单击数据：${event.data.item|json}；行索引：${event.data.index}"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            },
            "columns": [
                {
                    "name": "id",
                    "label": "ID",
                    "searchable": true
                },
                {
                    "name": "engine",
                    "label": "Rendering engine",
                    "filterable": {
                        "options": [
                            "Internet Explorer 4.0",
                            "Internet Explorer 5.0"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "browser",
                    "label": "Browser",
                    "sortable": true
                },
                {
                    "name": "platform",
                    "label": "Platform(s)"
                },
                {
                    "name": "version",
                    "label": "Engine version"
                },
                {
                    "name": "grade",
                    "label": "CSS grade"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
```

