TITLE: Configuring Row/Column Span in Table2 - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet configures an Amis Table2 component to demonstrate row and column spanning using `rowSpanExpr` and `colSpanExpr` properties within the `columns` array. The `rowSpanExpr` and `colSpanExpr` properties accept expressions that determine the span based on row index.  The table fetches data from an API and displays it with specified column configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/table2.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "api": "/api/sample?perPage=10",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "table2",
      "source": "$rows",
      "columns": [
        {
          "title": "Engine",
          "name": "engine"
        },
        {
          "title": "Version",
          "name": "version",
          "rowSpanExpr": "${ rowIndex === 2 ? 2 : 0 }"
        },
        {
          "title": "Browser",
          "name": "browser"
        },
        {
          "title": "Badge",
          "name": "badgeText",
          "colSpanExpr": "${ rowIndex === 6 ? 3 : 0 }"
        },
        {
          "title": "Grade",
          "name": "grade"
        },
        {
          "title": "Platform",
          "name": "platform"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

