TITLE: Configuring Table Row Double-Click Event in Amis
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure a double-click event on an entire row in an Amis table. When a row is double-clicked, it triggers a toast notification displaying the row data and index. The table fetches data from an API endpoint and defines columns with properties such as 'name', 'label', and 'searchable'.
