TITLE: Passing Data Between AMIS Actions
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema illustrates how to pass data between actions in AMIS. A button click event triggers a broadcast action with specified data. The subsequent form component listens for this broadcast event and reloads its data with the data received from the broadcast, demonstrating data transfer between events and actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/event-action.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: schema
CODE:
```
{
  type: 'page',
  body: [
    {
      type: 'button',
      id: 'b_001',
      label: '发一个广播，携带动作参数',
      className: 'mb-2',
      level: 'primary',
      onEvent: {
        click: {
          actions: [
            {
              actionType: 'broadcast',
              args: {
                eventName: 'broadcast_1',
              },
              data: {
                name: 'lvxj',
                age: 18
              },
              description: '一个按钮的点击事件'
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      type: 'form',
      name: 'form1',
      id: 'form_001',
      title: '接收广播事件的参数',
      debug: true,
      body: [
        {
          type: 'input-text',
          id: 'form_001_text_01',
          label: '年龄',
          name: 'age',
          disabled: false,
          mode: 'horizontal'
        }
      ],
      data: {
        name: 'amis'
      },
      onEvent: {
        broadcast_1: {
          actions: [
            {
              actionType: 'reload',
              data: {
                age: '${age}',
                name: '${name}'
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

