TITLE: Configuring rowDbClick Event for Input-Table
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure the `rowDbClick` event, which is triggered when a row is double-clicked. The configured action displays a toast message. The `addable` property enables the addition of rows which can then be double-clicked, thus triggering the `rowDbClick` event.
