TITLE: Registering Component for Inter-Communication
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to register a custom renderer component to be available for inter-component communication via a Scoped Context. This allows other components to find and interact with this component through its name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/custom-react.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import {Renderer, ScopedContext} from 'amis';
@Renderer({
  type: 'my-renderer'
})
export class CustomRenderer extends React.Component {
  static contextType = ScopedContext;

  constructor() {
    const scoped = this.context;
    scoped.registerComponent(this);
  }

  componentWillUnmount() {
    const scoped = this.context;
    scoped.unRegisterComponent(this);
  }

  // 其他部分省略了。
}
```

