TITLE: Spring Boot Backend Implementation for Log Streaming
DESCRIPTION: This Java code shows a Spring Boot controller that returns a `StreamingResponseBody`, which allows streaming log data to the client. It writes log messages to the output stream in a loop, flushing the stream after each write to ensure real-time delivery.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/log.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Controller
public class StreamingResponseBodyController {
    @GetMapping("/logs")
    public ResponseEntity<StreamingResponseBody> handleLog() {
        StreamingResponseBody stream = out -> {
          for (int i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
            String msg = "log" + " @ " + new Date();
            out.write(msg.getBytes());
            out.flush();
          }
          out.close();
        };
        return new ResponseEntity(stream, HttpStatus.OK);
    }
}
```

