TITLE: Defining Rounded Corner Styles in CSS
DESCRIPTION: This CSS snippet defines classes for creating rounded corners on elements. It uses the `@border-radius-base` variable for consistent radius values. It allows setting rounded corners for all corners or specific corners (top, right, bottom, left).
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/style.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
.r {
  border-radius: @border-radius-base @border-radius-base @border-radius-base
    @border-radius-base;
}
.r-2x {
  border-radius: @border-radius-base * 2;
}
.r-3x {
  border-radius: @border-radius-base * 3;
}
.r-l {
  border-radius: @border-radius-base 0 0 @border-radius-base;
}
.r-r {
  border-radius: 0 @border-radius-base @border-radius-base 0;
}
.r-t {
  border-radius: @border-radius-base @border-radius-base 0 0;
}
.r-b {
  border-radius: 0 0 @border-radius-base @border-radius-base;
}
```

