TITLE: Defining Radios Component in Amis Form
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the basic usage of the radios component within an Amis form. It defines a form with a radio button group labeled 'radios'. The radio group provides four options: OptionA, OptionB, OptionC, and OptionD, with corresponding values 'a', 'b', 'c', and 'd'. The `type` attribute is set to "radios" to specify the component type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/radios.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "body": [
    {
      "name": "radios",
      "type": "radios",
      "label": "radios",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "OptionA",
          "value": "a"
        },
        {
          "label": "OptionB",
          "value": "b"
        },
        {
          "label": "OptionC",
          "value": "c"
        },
        {
          "label": "OptionD",
          "value": "d"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

