TITLE: Using Namespace in Value Expressions - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema demonstrates how to use namespace within expressions to set default values for form items. The `value` attribute can contain expressions like `${window:document.title}`. It retrieves data from global objects, such as the browser's `document` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/formitem.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "label": "text",
      "name": "test1",
      "value": "${window:document.title}",
      "description": "默认值表达式支持namespace: ${window:document.title}"
    }
  ]
}
```

