TITLE: onClick Event with Return False - JavaScript (Prevent Dialog)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use `return false` within an `onClick` event handler to prevent subsequent AMIS actions from executing. In this case, it prevents the dialog from being displayed after the alert is shown. This is useful for controlling the order of execution and conditionally preventing actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/action.md#_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "label": "弹框",
  "type": "button",
  "actionType": "dialog",
  "onClick": "alert('点击按钮'); return false;",
  "dialog": {
    "title": "弹框",
    "body": "这是个简单的弹框。"
  }
}
```

