TITLE: Setting InputCity Value (Schema)
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates how to programmatically set the value of the InputCity component using the `setValue` action. A button triggers the `setValue` action on the InputCity component with the ID `setvalue_text`, setting the value to `110100`. The `args` property defines the `value` to be set.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-city.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "debug": true,
    "body": [
        {
            "name": "city",
            "type": "input-city",
            "label": "城市",
            "id": "setvalue_text",
            "value": "110000"
        },
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": "赋值",
            "onEvent": {
                "click": {
                    "actions": [
                        {
                            "actionType": "setValue",
                            "componentId": "setvalue_text",
                            "args": {
                                "value": "110100"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

