TITLE: Initializing Timeline with Unified Card Schema and Data (AMIS)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates using a unified `cardSchema` at the timeline level to render all timeline items as cards with a consistent structure. It uses data binding to populate card properties like title, subtitle, and description from the timeline item's data.  The `cardSchema` defines a card structure with a header and body, referencing data from the timeline items. Some items also contain a specific cardSchema that will override the general one for that item.
