TITLE: Updating/Resetting Nav Items with Actions
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the usage of `updateItems` and `reset` actions to manipulate the Nav component's data source. It demonstrates how to update the navigation data to show only the children of a specific item and how to reset the data source back to the original state. Requires amis.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/nav.md#_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "items": [
      {
        "label": "Nav 1",
        "to": "/docs/index",
        "icon": "fa fa-user"
      },
      {
        "label": "Nav 2",
        "unfolded": true,
        "active": true,
        "children": [
          {
            "label": "Nav 2-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "label": "Nav 2-1-1",
                "to": "/docs/api-2-1-1"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "label": "Nav 2-2",
            "to": "/docs/api-2-2"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "label": "Nav 3",
        "to": "/docs/renderers"
      }
    ]
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "container",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "action",
        "label": "设置数据源",
        "onEvent": {
          "click": {
            "actions": [
              {
                "actionType": "updateItems",
                "args": {
                  "value": "Nav 2"
                },
                "componentId": "asideNav"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      },
