TITLE: Configuring Row Mouse Leave Event in Amis CRUD
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure the 'rowMouseLeave' event in an Amis CRUD component. When the mouse leaves a row, a toast message is displayed showing the row index. The 'onEvent' property defines the event listener, and the 'actions' array specifies the actions to be performed when the event is triggered. The 'event.data.index' expression accesses the index of the row.
