TITLE: Value Expression vs Name Mapping Priority - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema demonstrates the priority between value expressions and name mapping when setting default values for form items. If both a value expression `${xxx}` and name mapping are defined, the value expression takes precedence. If the `value` is a normal string, then name mapping occurs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/formitem.md#_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "debug": true,
  "data":{
    "item1": "hello world!",
    "item2": "hello amis!",
    "item3": "hello amis-editor!"
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "label": "test1",
      "name": "test1",
      "value": "123",
      "description": "普通value默认值"
    },
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "label": "test2",
      "name": "item1",
      "description": "关联数据域中的item1"
    },
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "label": "test3",
      "name": "item2",
      "value": "345",
      "description": "非value表达式（\\${xxx}），则优先使用name映射"
    },
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "label": "test4",
      "name": "item3",
      "value": "${test1}",
      "description": "value表达式（\\${xxx}）优先级最高"
    }
  ]
}
```

