TITLE: GraphQL Query with Data and Variables (AMIS <= 1.7.0)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to perform a GraphQL mutation in AMIS versions 1.7.0 and earlier. It utilizes the `data` property with `query` and `variables` fields to specify the GraphQL mutation and its corresponding variables.  The `name` and `email` variables are dynamically populated from input fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/types/api.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "api": {
    "method": "post",
    "url": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
    "data": {
      "query": "mutation AddUser($name: String!, $email: String!) { \
        insert_user(object: { title: $title, email: $email }) { \
          title \
          email \
        } \
      }",
      "variables": {
         "name": "${name}",
         "email": "${email}"
      }
    }
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "name": "name",
      "label": "姓名："
    },
    {
      "name": "email",
      "type": "input-email",
      "label": "邮箱："
    }
  ]
}
```

