TITLE: AMIS Opening a Modal Dialog
DESCRIPTION: This AMIS configuration demonstrates how to open a modal dialog using the 'dialog' action type within an event handler. The configuration defines the dialog content, title, and data. Event handlers for 'confirm' and 'cancel' events within the dialog trigger corresponding 'toast' actions to display messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/event-action.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  type: 'page',
  body: [
    {
      type: 'button',
      className: 'ml-2',
      label: '打开弹窗（模态）',
      level: 'primary',
      onEvent: {
        click: {
          actions: [
            {
              actionType: 'dialog',
              dialog: {
                type: 'dialog',
                title: '模态弹窗',
                id: 'dialog_001',
                data: {
                  myage: '22'
                },
                body: [
                  {
                    type: 'tpl',
                    tpl: '<p>对，你打开了模态弹窗</p>',
                    inline: false
                  },
                  {
                    type: 'input-text',
                    name: 'myname',
                    mode: 'horizontal',
                    onEvent: {
                      change: {
                        actions: [
                          {
                            actionType: 'confirm',
                            componentId: 'dialog_001'
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }
                  }
                ],
                onEvent: {
                  confirm: {
                    actions: [
                      {
                        actionType: 'toast',
                        args: {
                          msg: 'confirm'
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  cancel: {
                    actions: [
                      {
                        actionType: 'toast',
                        args: {
                          msg: 'cancel'
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

