TITLE: Configuring Asynchronous Custom JS Action (Thunk) with Amis Schema
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to configure an asynchronous 'custom' action that returns a Thunk function. This allows performing asynchronous operations using a callback-based approach within the custom JavaScript code. The event.setData is used to update the data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/event-action.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  type: 'page',
  body: [
    {
      "type": "form",
      "title": "表单",
      "body": [
        {
          "label": "编号",
          "type": "input-text",
          "name": "pId",
          "id": "u:e47e2c8e6be7",
          "mode": "horizontal",
          "addOn": {
            "label": "自动获取",
            "type": "button",
            "onEvent": {
              "click": {
                "actions": [
                  {
                    "componentId": "u:52cd013e120e",
                    "actionType": "disabled"
                  },
                  {
                    "script": "return (callback) => { setTimeout(() => {event.setData({...event.data, pId: '01027359' });callback();}, 3000) };",
                    "actionType": "custom"
                  },
                  {
                    "componentId": "u:e47e2c8e6be7",
                    "args": {
                      "value": "${pId}"
                    },
                    "actionType": "setValue"
                  },
                  {
                    "componentId": "u:52cd013e120e",
                    "actionType": "enabled"
                  }
                ],
                "weight": 0
              }
            },
            "id": "u:52cd013e120e"
          }
        }
      ],
      "apiFromAPICenter": false,
      "id": "u:76203156676a"
    }
  ]
}
```

