TITLE: Configuring Default Expandable Rows (Amis JSON)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of the `expandable` property to enable row expansion in an Amis `table2` component. It shows how to define which rows can be expanded using `expandableOn`, the key field with `keyField`, and the default expanded rows using `expandedRowKeys`. It also shows how to customize the expanded row with a container and a template.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/table2.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "service",
  "api": "/api/sample?perPage=5",
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "table2",
      "source": "$rows",
      "columns": [
        {
          "title": "Engine",
          "name": "engine"
        },
        {
          "title": "Version",
          "name": "version"
        },
        {
          "title": "Browser",
          "name": "browser"
        },
        {
          "title": "Operation",
          "name": "operation",
          "type": "button",
          "label": "删除",
          "size": "sm"
        }
      ],
      "expandable": {
        "expandableOn": "this.record && (this.record.id === 1 || this.record.id === 3)",
        "keyField": "id",
        "expandedRowClassNameExpr": "${ rowIndex === 2 ? 'bg-success' : '' }",
        "expandedRowKeys": ["3"],
        "type": "container",
        "body": [
          {
            "type": "tpl",
            "html": "<div class=\"test\">测试测试</div>"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

