TITLE: InputDateRange Transform Function (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet defines a 'transform' function for the InputDateRange component that sets the hours, minutes, seconds, and milliseconds of the end date to the current time, effectively overriding the default behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-date-range.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
function transform(value, config, props, data) {
  const now = moment();

  if (config.type === 'end') {
    value.set({
      hours: now.hours(),
      minutes: now.minutes(),
      seconds: now.seconds(),
      milliseconds: now.milliseconds()
    });
  }

  return value;
}
```

