TITLE: Triggering Cancel Action on Dialog with JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates how to trigger the "cancel" action on a dialog from another component (in this case, a button within the dialog itself). The button's `onEvent` configuration specifies an action of type "cancel" targeting the dialog with the ID "dialog_cancel". This allows for custom cancellation logic to be executed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/dialog.md#_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "button",
    "label": "弹个表单",
    "actionType": "dialog",
    "dialog": {
        "title": "在弹框中的表单",
        "id": "dialog_cancel",
        "body": {
          "type": "form",
          "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm?waitSeconds=2",
          "body": [
              {
                  "type": "input-text",
                  "name": "username",
                  "required": true,
                  "placeholder": "请输入用户名",
                  "label": "用户名"
              },
              {
                  "type": "input-password",
                  "name": "password",
                  "label": "密码",
                  "required": true,
                  "placeholder": "请输入密码"
              },
              {
                  "type": "checkbox",
                  "name": "rememberMe",
                  "label": "记住登录"
              }
          ]
        },
        "actions": [
          {
            "type": "button",
            "label": "触发取消",
            "onEvent": {
              "click": {
                "actions": [
                  {
                    "actionType": "cancel",
                    "componentId": "dialog_cancel"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        ]
    }
}
```

