TITLE: Listening to Broadcast Events - TypeScript/JSX
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to listen for broadcast events in a React component rendering an Amis configuration. It utilizes the `onBroadcast` prop of the `renderAmis` function to handle custom events like `formSubmited`. The component relies on the Amis library and expects the event type, raw event, and event data as inputs to the `handleBroadcast` function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/ui-library.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {render as renderAmis} from 'amis';

function DemoComponent() {
  function handleBroadcast(type: string, rawEvent: any, data: any) {
    console.log(type);
    if (type === 'formSubmited') {
      console.log('内部表单提交了');
    }
  }

  return <div>
    {renderAmis(amisJSON, {onBroadcast: handleBroadcast})}
  </div>
};
```

