TITLE: Updating AMIS Schema
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to update the AMIS schema using the `updateSchema` method of the `amisScoped` object.  It dynamically changes the content of the page body from an initial string to 'changed' when the button is clicked.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/start/getting-started.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
let amisJSON = {
  type: 'page',
  body: [
    'inital string',

    {
      type: 'button',
      label: 'Change',
      onClick: handleChange
    }
  ]
};
let amisScoped = amis.embed('#root', amisJSON);

function handleChange() {
  const schema = {
    ...amisJSON,
    body: ['changed']
  };
  amisScoped.updateSchema(schema);
}
```

