TITLE: MyRenderer Component Definition
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a simple React component named `MyRenderer` that displays a greeting message with a configurable target. It also supports setting width and height via props, which are used for enabling drag-resize functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/editor.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
@Renderer({
  type: 'my-renderer',
  name: 'my-renderer'
})
export class MyRenderer extends React.Component {
  static defaultProps = {
    target: 'world'
  };

  render() {
    const {target, width, height} = this.props;

    return (
      <p style={{width: width || 'auto', height: height || 'auto'}}>
        Hello {target}!
      </p>
    );
  }
}
```

