TITLE: Setting Precision for InputNumber - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema shows how to configure the precision and step for an InputNumber component in an Amis form. The `precision` property sets the number of decimal places, while `step` defines the increment/decrement value. It also includes a field with only `step` defined to demonstrate the derived precision.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/input-number.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "form",
    "debug": true,
    "api": "/api/mock2/form/saveForm",
    "data": {
        "number2": 3.1234
    },
    "body": [
        {
            "type": "input-number",
            "name": "number1",
            "label": "数字",
            "precision": 2,
            "step": 0.01,
            "value": 2.98786
        },
        {
            "type": "input-number",
            "name": "number2",
            "label": "数字2",
            "precision": 3,
            "step": 0.001
        },
        {
            "type": "input-number",
            "name": "number3",
            "label": "数字3",
            "step": 0.001,
            "description": "不设置precision，仅设置step, 实际精度为3"
        }
    ]
}
```

