TITLE: XLOOKUP Example
DESCRIPTION: This formula utilizes XLOOKUP to find a value in the 'Sales_1' table. It searches for the value in cell $G7 within the 'Region' column of the 'Sales_1' table and returns the corresponding value from the 'Jan' column. XLOOKUP is a modern and flexible lookup function. The value in the first Region column is looked up and the corresponding January sales value is returned.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/packages/office-viewer/src/excel/formula/__tests__/data/testformulas/structured_references.txt#_snippet_51

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
=XLOOKUP($G7,Sales_1[[Region]:[Region]],Sales_1[Jan])
```

