TITLE: Data Chain Example with Service Component
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the concept of data chains by using a `service` component to encapsulate and provide data to its child components. The outer `tpl` component accesses data from the parent (`page`) component, while the inner `tpl` accesses data from the `service` component and falls back to the parent for missing values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/datascope-and-datachain.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "name": "zhangsan",
    "age": 20
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "tpl",
      "tpl": "my name is ${name}"
    },
    {
      "type": "service",
      "data": {
        "name": "lisi"
      },
      "body":  {
        "type": "tpl",
        "tpl": "my name is ${name}, I'm ${age} years old"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

