TITLE: Truncate Filter Usage
DESCRIPTION: Truncates a string if it exceeds a certain length, adding a mask at the end. The 'length' parameter specifies the maximum length (default 200), and 'mask' specifies the string to display when truncated (default '...') . Input is a string. Output is a truncated string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/data-mapping.md#_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
${xxx | truncate[:length][:mask]}
```

