TITLE: Temporary React Component Extension
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a temporary React component within an Amis JSON configuration.  The `children` property defines a function that returns JSX, allowing custom rendering and logic.  The function receives `value`, `onChange`, and `data` parameters for component interaction and data access.  The `asFormItem` property allows the component to behave like a form item.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/custom-react.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "title": "自定义组件示例",
  "body": {
    "type": "form",
    "body": [
      {
        "type": "input-text",
        "label": "用户名",
        "name": "usename"
      },
      {
        "name": "mycustom",
        "asFormItem": true,
        "children": ({value, onChange, data}) => (
          <div>
            <p>这个是个自定义组件</p>
            <p>当前值：{value}</p>
            <a className="btn btn-default" onClick={
              () => onChange(Math.round(Math.random() * 10000))
            }>随机修改</a>
          </div>
        )
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

