TITLE: Custom Renderer with Children
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a custom React renderer that supports child components.  The `render` prop from `this.props` is used to render the child nodes. The `region` parameter specifies the area to render the child, `node` represents the child node itself, and `props` allows communication with the child.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/custom-react.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import {Renderer} from 'amis';

@Renderer({
  type: 'my-renderer2'
})
class CustomRenderer extends React.Component {
  render() {
    const {tip, body, render} = this.props;
    return (
      <div>
        <p>这是自定义组件：{tip}</p>
        {body ? (
          <div className="container">
            {render('body', body, {
              // 这里的信息会作为 props 传递给子组件，一般情况下都不需要这个
            })}
          </div>
        ) : null}
      </div>
    );
  }
}
```

