TITLE: Pick Filter JSON Schema Example
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the use of the 'pick' filter to select values from objects and arrays of objects within an Amis JSON schema. Includes examples of extracting a single key value, iterating over an array of objects to get the specified key, and renaming keys using tilde.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/data-mapping.md#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "a": 1,
      "b": 2,
      "c": 3
    }
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "tpl",
    "tpl": "a value of object is ${object|pick:a}" // 输出: a value of object is 1
  }
}
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "array": [
      {
        "a": 1,
        "b": 2,
        "c": 3
      },
      {
        "a": 10,
        "b": 20,
        "c": 30
      },
      {
        "a": 100,
        "b": 200,
        "c": 300
      }
    ]
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "tpl",
    "tpl": "new array is ${array|pick:a|json}" // 输出: new array is [1, 10 ,100]
  }
}
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "array": [
      {
        "aaa": 1,
        "bbb": 2,
        "ccc": 3
      },
      {
        "aaa": 10,
        "bbb": 20,
        "ccc": 30
      },
      {
        "aaa": 100,
        "bbb": 200,
        "ccc": 300
      }
    ]
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "tpl",
    "tpl": "new array is ${array|pick:a~aaa,b~bbb|json}"
    // 输出: new array is  [ { "a": 1, "b": 2 }, { "a": 10, "b": 20 }, { "a": 100, "b": 200 } ]
  }
}
```

