TITLE: Replacing URL in Amis Configuration (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the `replaceText` property within the `env` parameter of the `amis.embed` function to dynamically replace parts of a URL. This is useful for switching between development and production environments, where the host address differs.  It relies on the `amisRequire` function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/start/faq.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let amis = amisRequire('amis/embed');
let amisJSON = {
  type: 'page',
  body: {
    type: 'service',
    api: 'HOST/api'
  }
};
let amisScoped = amis.embed(
  '#root',
  amisJSON,
  {},
  {
    replaceText: {
      HOST: 'http://localhost'
    }
  }
);
```

