TITLE: Carousel Action Triggering - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to trigger actions on a carousel component from another component, such as a button.  It uses the 'actionType' property with values like 'next' to control the carousel. The 'componentId' property specifies the ID of the target carousel. This example shows a button that, when clicked, advances the carousel to the next image.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/carousel.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
[
  {
    "type": "action",
    "label": "下一张",
    "className": "mr-3 mb-3",
    "onEvent": {
      "click": {
        "actions": [
          {
            "actionType": "next",
            "componentId": "carousel_001"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "carousel",
    "id": "carousel_001",
    "auto": false,
    "thumbMode": "cover",
    "animation": "slide",
    "height": 300,
