TITLE: Listening to Events in Amis - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to listen for various events within an Amis form, such as input changes, form submissions, and button clicks. It defines an Amis JSON configuration with event handlers for input's `onChange`, form's `onFinished`, and button's `onClick` events. Dependencies include the Amis framework. The expected input is the event data and the Amis form context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/ui-library.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let amisJSON = {
  type: 'page',
  title: '表单页面',
  body: [
    {
      type: 'form',
      mode: 'horizontal',
      onFinished: values => {
        console.log('form', values);
        return false; // 这样可以禁掉 amis 后续的默认行为
      },
      body: [
        {
          label: 'Name',
          type: 'input-text',
          name: 'name',
          onChange: value => {
            console.log('Name', value);
          }
        },
        {
          type: 'button',
          label: '按钮修改',
          onClick: (e, props) => {
            console.log('消息通知');
            props.formStore.setValues({name: 'amis'});
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
```

