TITLE: Refreshing specific rows in AMIS CRUD
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to refresh a specific row in an AMIS CRUD component using the `deferApi` property and specifying the `args.condition` parameter in the `reload` action. It requires AMIS version 6.3.0 or higher. The `condition` is used to identify the row to be refreshed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/crud.md#_snippet_102

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "name": "amis",
    "age": 18,
    "date": "2023-6-6"
  },
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "button",
      "label": "刷新 id 为 2 的行",
      level: 'primary',
      "className": "mb-2",
      "onEvent": {
        "click": {
          "actions": [
            {
              "componentId": "crud_reload1",
              "actionType": "reload",
              "args": {
                "condition": "${id == 2}"
              }
            },

            {
              "componentId": "crud_reload1",
              "actionType": "setExpanded",
              "args": {
                "condition": "${id == 2}",
                "value": true
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "crud",
      "api": "/api/mock2/crud/table6",
      "deferApi": "/api/mock2/crud/table6?parentId=${id}&waitSeconds=2",
      "id": "crud_reload1",
      "syncLocation": false,
      "columns": [
        {
          "name": "id",
          "label": "ID"
        },
        {
          "name": "engine",
          "label": "Rendering engine"
        },
        {
          "name": "browser",
          "label": "Browser"
        },
        {
          "name": "platform",
          "label": "Platform(s)"
        },
        {
          "name": "version",
          "label": "Engine version"
        },
        {
          "name": "grade",
          "label": "CSS grade"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

