TITLE: Configure Container Style for Line Breaks (Amis Schema)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure a container component in Amis to handle line breaks by setting the `white-space` CSS property to `pre`. This ensures that newline characters (`\n`) in the data are rendered as line breaks in the user interface. The snippet includes a `page` with a `container` and a nested `tpl` component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/start/faq.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "log": "line 1\nline 2"
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "container",
    "style": {
      "white-space": "pre"
    },
    "body": {
      "type": "tpl",
      "tpl": "${log}"
    }
  }
}
```

