TITLE: Complex Conditional Lookup with Date and #REF
DESCRIPTION: This formula performs a complex conditional lookup based on date and checks for 'N/A'. It uses nested IF statements along with MONTH and VLOOKUP functions, utilizing ranges from the 'Gas Curves' sheet. The formula incorporates a #REF element related to TRUE comparison, which should be resolved or replaced with a boolean to ensure formula accuracy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/packages/office-viewer/src/excel/formula/__tests__/data/enron/knownfails.txt#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
IF(A39="N/A"," ",IF(=TRUE,(IF(MONTH(A39)>=4,IF(MONTH(A39)<=10,VLOOKUP(A39,Gas Curves!B17:O377,13),VLOOKUP(A39,Gas Curves!B17:O377,14)),VLOOKUP(A39,Gas Curves!B17:O377,14))),0))
```

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
IF(=7,AVERAGE(C38:C44),IF(=14,AVERAGE(C31:C44),IF(=30,AVERAGE(C15:C44),IF(=40,AVERAGE(C4:C44),0))))
```

