TITLE: Adding Form Validation Rule - JSSDK - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to add a custom form validation rule to the Amis framework using the JSSDK. It defines a validation function that checks if the input value is one of the four direct-controlled municipalities in China (Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin, Chongqing). The `addRule` function registers the validation rule with a name, validation function, and error message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/addon.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let amisLib = amisRequire('amis');
amisLib.addRule(
  // 校验名
  'isZXS',
  // 校验函数，values 是表单里所有表单项的值，可用于做联合校验；value 是当前表单项的值
  (values, value) => {
    if (
      value === '北京' ||
      value === '上海' ||
      value === '天津' ||
      value === '重庆'
    ) {
      // return true 表示校验通过
      return true;
    }
    // return false 表示校验不通过，会进行错误提示
    return false;
  },
  // 出错时的报错信息
  '输入的不是直辖市'
);
```

