TITLE: Registering a Custom Form Item
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to register a custom React component as an Amis form item using the `@FormItem` decorator. This simplifies the process of creating custom form controls. The component only needs to handle displaying the current value and responding to user interaction to set the new value. The `amis` library handles label presentation, form validation, and layout.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/custom-react.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import {FormItem} from 'amis';

@FormItem({
  type: 'custom'
})
class MyFormItem extends React.Component {
  render() {
    const {value, onChange} = this.props;

    return (
      <div>
        <p>这个是个自定义组件</p>
        <p>当前值：{value}</p>
        <a
          className="btn btn-default"
          onClick={() => onChange(Math.round(Math.random() * 10000))}
        >
          随机修改
        </a>
      </div>
    );
  }
}
```

