TITLE: ReplaceText with Ignore Keys (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to use the `replaceTextIgnoreKeys` option in conjunction with `replaceText` to prevent certain keys from being replaced.  The example shows both a static array and a function to filter keys that should be ignored. This prevents unintended replacements in specific fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/start/getting-started.md#_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let amisScoped = amis.embed(
  '#root',
  {
    type: 'page',
    body: {
      type: 'service',
      api: 'service/api'
    }
  },
  {},
  {
    replaceText: {
      service: 'http://localhost'
    },
    // replaceTextIgnoreKeys: ['api']，
    replaceTextIgnoreKeys: key => key === 'api'
  }
);
```

