TITLE: Data Adaptation Logic - Javascript
DESCRIPTION: This javascript snippet serves as the adaptor function for the `initApi` configuration, processing the data retrieved from the API endpoint. It filters the data into `trainList` (grade X) and `serviceList` (grade C) and returns them along with the complete `allList` data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/picker.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const data = payload.data.rows || payload.result.rows;
console.log(' data', data)
const trainList = data.filter(item => item.grade === 'X');
const serviceList = data.filter(item => item.grade === 'C');
return {
  allList: data,
  trainList,
  serviceList,
};
```

