TITLE: Using Data Provider with Function Type in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates using the `dataProvider` property with a function to set up an interval for updating data and returning a cleanup function to clear the interval when the component is destroyed. `setData` is used to update data and `clearInterval` is used for cleanup. This example can only be used in jssdk or react projects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/service.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
    "type": "service",
    "dataProvider": (data, setData) => {
      const timer = setInterval(() => {
        setData({date: new Date().toString()})
      }, 1000);
      return () => { clearInterval(timer) }
    },
    "body": {
        "type": "tpl",
        "tpl": "现在是：${now}"
    }
}
```

