TITLE: Reload Form Data - Amis JSON
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the `reload` action to refresh a form component's data. When the button is clicked, it triggers a `reload` action targeting the form with id 'form_reload', which re-fetches data from the `initApi` endpoint.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/index.md#_snippet_42

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
[ { "type": "button", "label": "刷新表单", className: "mb-2", "onEvent": { "click": { "actions": [ { "actionType": "reload", "componentId": "form_reload" } ] } } }, { "type": "form", "id": "form_reload", "debug": true, "initApi": "/api/mock2/form/initData", "body": [ { "type": "input-text", "name": "name", "label": "姓名：" }, { "name": "author", "type": "input-text", "label": "作者：" } ] } ]
```

