TITLE: Build Editor Toolbar
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to add a custom toolbar item to the editor when a component is selected. It uses the `buildEditorToolbar` method to add an item that inserts a component before the selected one. It also demonstrates how to call `this.manager.showInsertPanel` to display the insert panel.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/editor.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
buildEditorToolbar(context: BaseEventContext, toolbars: Array<BasicToolbarItem>) {
  toolbars.push({
    iconSvg: 'left-arrow-to-left',
    tooltip: '向前插入组件',
    // level: 'special',
    placement: 'bottom',
    // placement: vertical ? 'bottom' : 'right',
    // className: vertical
    //   ? 'ae-InsertBefore is-vertical'
    //   : 'ae-InsertBefore',
    onClick: () =>
      this.manager.showInsertPanel(
        regionNode.region,
        regionNode.id,
        regionNode.preferTag,
        'insert',
        undefined,
        id
      )
  });
}
```

