TITLE: Percent Filter JSON Schema Example
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the usage of the 'percent' filter within an Amis JSON schema.  The example shows how to format a decimal value as a percentage with and without specifying the number of decimal places.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/data-mapping.md#_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "value": 0.8232343
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "tpl",
    "tpl": "value is ${value|percent}" // 输出: value is 82%
  }
}
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "value": 0.8232343
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "tpl",
    "tpl": "value is ${value|percent:2}" // 保留小数点后4位，输出: value is 82.32%
  }
}
```

