TITLE: Subtotaling a Column's Values (Filtered)
DESCRIPTION: These formulas use the SUBTOTAL function with code 109 to sum values within a column, taking into account visible cells after filtering. It's useful for calculating sums dynamically when rows are hidden by a filter. Each formula references different month columns [Jan], [Feb], and [Mar].
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/packages/office-viewer/src/excel/formula/__tests__/data/testformulas/structured_references.txt#_snippet_50

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
=SUBTOTAL(109,[Jan])
```

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
=SUBTOTAL(109,[Feb])
```

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
=SUBTOTAL(109,[Mar])
```

