TITLE: Conditional Calculation with Bollinger String
DESCRIPTION: This formula checks if a cell equals "BOLLINGER". If it does, it subtracts $AH755 from $J755; otherwise, it returns 0.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/packages/office-viewer/src/excel/formula/__tests__/data/enron/knownfails.txt#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
IF(="BOLLINGER",$J755-$AH755,0)
```

