TITLE: Escaping Template String Characters
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to escape special characters in Amis template strings.  To output the literal string `${xxx}` or `$xxx`, you need to escape the `$` character with a backslash: `\${xxx}`. This prevents Amis from interpreting the string as a data mapping expression.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/concepts/data-mapping.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: schema
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
    "name": "rick"
  },
  "body": {
    "type": "tpl",
    "tpl": "my name is \\${name}"
  }
}
```

