TITLE: Configuring deleteFail Event for Input-Table
DESCRIPTION: This configuration showcases the `deleteFail` event, triggered when deleting a row results in an error from the `deleteApi` call. A toast message alerts the user to the failure. The `deleteApi` is the key to triggering this event upon receiving an error response.
