TITLE: Conditional Calculation - Excel Formula
DESCRIPTION: This Excel formula performs a conditional calculation. It checks if the value in cell A8 is greater than 0. If true, it calculates 12 times the value in cell B2, then subtracts the value in cell D8.  If A8 is not greater than 0, the formula returns the string "0".
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/packages/office-viewer/src/excel/formula/__tests__/data/testformulas/user_contributed.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
IF(A8>0,12*$B$2-D8,"0")
```

