TITLE: Box Sizing Example - HTML
DESCRIPTION: This HTML snippet demonstrates the difference between `box-border` and `box-content`. The `box-border` div maintains a total height and width of 128px (h-32, w-32), including padding and border. The `box-content` div has a content area of 128px, plus padding and border, resulting in a larger total size. The example uses Tailwind CSS classes for styling.
