TITLE: Alert Level with Expression - JSON Schema
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use expressions to dynamically set the `level` of the Alert component based on data.  The `IFS` function is used to determine the level based on the `status` value. Requires Amis version 1.6.4 or later. It is part of a page schema that includes data and a body.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/alert.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{ "type": "page", "data": { "status": 1 }, "body": [ { "type": "alert", "level": "${IFS(status===1, 'danger', status===2, 'warning')}", "body": "这是内容区" } ] }
