TITLE: FormItem State Switch with Events JSON
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to switch a FormItem's state between input and static display using event actions. The example includes a button toolbar with two buttons: one to switch to input mode and another to switch to static mode. The `actionType` attributes `nonstatic` and `static` are used to toggle the component's state. The `componentId` links the buttons to the target form item.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/form/formitem.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "form",
  "title": "单个表单项状态切换",
  "mode": "horizontal",
  "labelWidth": 220,
  "body": [
    {
      "type": "input-text",
      "id": "formItemSwitch",
      "name": "var1",
      "label": "使用事件动作状态切换",
      "value": "text"
    },
    {
      "type": 'button-toolbar',
      "name": 'button-toolbar',
      "buttons": [
        {
          "type": "button",
          "label": "输入态",
          "level": "primary",
          "onEvent": {
            "click": {
              "actions": [
                {
                  "actionType": "nonstatic",
                  "componentId": "formItemSwitch"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "button",
          "label": "展示态",
          "level": "primary",
          "onEvent": {
            "click": {
              "actions": [
                {
                  "actionType": "static",
                  "componentId": "formItemSwitch"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "className": 'show'
    },
  ],
  "actions": []
}
```

