TITLE: Backend Implementation for WebSocket Server in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates a basic WebSocket server implementation using the `ws` library. It sets up a server that sends random number data to connected clients every 500 milliseconds. The data is formatted as a JSON string before sending.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/components/service.md#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const WebSocket = require('ws');

const ws = new WebSocket.Server({port: 8777});

ws.on('connection', function connection(ws) {
  setInterval(() => {
    const random = Math.floor(Math.random() * Math.floor(100));
    // 返回给 amis 的数据
    const data = {
      random
    };
    // 发送前需要转成字符串
    ws.send(JSON.stringify(data));
  }, 500);
});
```

