TITLE: Accessing Submission Data in Tracker Function (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to access the submission data within the tracker function. The `data` parameter passed to the tracker function contains the submission data, which can be logged or processed as needed. This enables access to the submission data for the API events, which is not included in the `eventData` to prevent information leaks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/tracker.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
  tracker: (eventTrack, data) => {
    console.log('提交数据详情', data);
    const blob = new Blob([JSON.stringify(eventTrack)], {
      type: 'application/json'
    });
    navigator.sendBeacon('/tracker', blob);
  };
}
```

