TITLE: Escaping Special Characters in Value - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema shows how to escape special characters in the `value` attribute to display literal text.  To output literal `${xxx}`, escape the `$` character with a backslash: `\${xxx}`. This prevents the expression from being evaluated and displays it as plain text.
