TITLE: SchemaArray Configuration Example in Amis
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the usage of SchemaArray in Amis, where the 'body' property is configured with an array of Schema objects.  Each Schema object defines a Tpl component that renders a template string, allowing multiple components to be rendered within the same node level.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/types/schemanode.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "page",
  "data": {
      "name": "amis",
      "age": 1
  },
  "body": [
      {
        "type":"tpl",
        "tpl": "my name is ${name}" // 输出 my name is amis
      },
      {
        "type":"tpl",
        "tpl": "I am ${age} years old" // 输出 I am 1 years old
      }
  ]
}
```

