TITLE: InputText Component with Renderer Decorator
DESCRIPTION: This JSX code shows the implementation of an InputText component in AMIS using the Renderer decorator. The 'type' property in the decorator specifies the component type.  The render function renders the input element, binding an onChange handler to update the value. It uses label and name from the props.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/internal.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
@Renderer({
    type: 'input-text'
    // ... 其他信息隐藏了
})
export class FormItemTextRenderer extends React.Component {
    // ... 其他信息隐藏了
    render() {
        const {
            label,
            name,
            onChange
        } = this.props;
        return (
            <div className="form-group">
                <label>{label}<label>
                <input type="text" onChange={(e) => onChange(e.currentTarget.value)} />
            </div>
        );
    }
}
```

