TITLE: Conditional IF with Error Handling and #REF
DESCRIPTION: This formula uses a nested IF statement with error handling (ISERROR) and a condition based on cell A71. It includes calculations involving a cell referenced by #REF and a named range 'Include1'. The nested IF handles 'N/A' values and potential errors, multiplying by 'Include1' or returning #REF based on conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/packages/office-viewer/src/excel/formula/__tests__/data/enron/knownfails.txt#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
IF(A71="N/A"," ",IF(ISERROR(#REF),K59*Include1,#REF))
```

LANGUAGE: Excel Formula
CODE:
```
IF(A71="N/A"," ",IF(ISERROR(#REF),L59*Include1,IF(#REF=0,L59*Include1,#REF)))
```

