TITLE: Initializing Amis with Tracker Function in Javascript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to initialize an Amis application with a custom tracker function. The tracker function captures user interaction events and sends them to a specified endpoint using `navigator.sendBeacon`. The `eventTrack` parameter contains information about the event, and the `props` parameter provides access to component properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/baidu/amis/blob/master/docs/zh-CN/extend/tracker.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
amis.embed(
  '#root',
  {
    // amis schema
  },
  {
    // 这里是初始 props
  },
  {
    tracker: (eventTrack, props) => {
      const blob = new Blob([JSON.stringify(eventTrack)], {
        type: 'application/json'
      });
      navigator.sendBeacon('/tracker', blob);
    }
  }
);
```

